</h3><p class="sc-kHOZwM oQMan pf-21_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">First aid training in the early years is crucial for compliance with health and safety regulations and for the peace of mind, it brings to staff and parents. Knowing that educators and carers can competently handle medical emergencies can significantly impact the care and safety of children.




















</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-iqseJM ducrfW pf-23_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-24_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-bTfYFJ fFWOZc pf-25_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key facts and statistics
</h3><p class="sc-kHOZwM oQMan pf-27_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">According to data from the Health and Safety Executive (HSE), over 15,000 injuries were reported in educational settings in the UK last year alone. Many of these involved young children and could have been mitigated with prompt first aid response.




















</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-iqseJM ducrfW pf-29_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-30_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-bTfYFJ fFWOZc pf-31_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key definitions
</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-kYHfwS lkFAWj pf-33_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah hUMvDY pf-34_ pf-text-1"><strong>First aid </strong>- The immediate assistance given to any person suffering from either a minor or serious illness or injury, with care provided to preserve life, prevent the condition from worsening, or promote recovery.



































</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah hUMvDY pf-36_ pf-text-1"><strong>Early years setting</strong> - Any environment that provides education and care to children from birth to five years old, including nurseries, preschools, and childminders.




































</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-iqseJM ducrfW pf-38_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-39_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-bTfYFJ fFWOZc pf-40_ pf-heading-1-h3">Relevant legislation and regulations
</h3><p class="sc-kHOZwM oQMan pf-42_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The importance of first aid in early years is underscored by various legislative frameworks and guidelines:
























</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-kYHfwS lkFAWj pf-44_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah hUMvDY pf-45_ pf-text-1"><strong>The Health and Safety (First-Aid) Regulations 1981 </strong>- These regulations require employers to provide adequate and appropriate equipment, facilities, and personnel to ensure employees receive immediate attention if they are injured or taken ill at work.




































</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah hUMvDY pf-47_ pf-text-1"><strong>Early Years Foundation Stage (EYFS) framework </strong>- This framework mandates that at least one person with a current paediatric first aid certificate must be on the premises when children are present.




































</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-iqseJM ducrfW pf-49_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-50_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-bTfYFJ fFWOZc pf-51_ pf-heading-1-h3">Best practices in first aid training
