</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-iqseJM ducrfW pf-84_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-85_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-bTfYFJ fFWOZc pf-86_ pf-heading-1-h3">Recommendations
</h3><p class="sc-kHOZwM oQMan pf-88_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">To enhance the effectiveness of first aid training in early years, it is recommended that:



























</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-kYHfwS lkFAWj pf-90_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah hUMvDY pf-91_ pf-text-1"><strong>All staff are trained </strong>- Beyond the minimum requirement, all staff members should be trained in paediatric first aid.






































